One-eyed police killer Dale Cregan has been moved to the same psychiatric hospital as Moors murderer Ian Brady after going on hunger strike for the second time .
The 31-year-old has reportedly been transferred from HMP Manchester , formerly Strangeways , to Ashworth Hospital , a high-security psychiatric unit in Maghull , Merseyside .
Cregan , who was jailed for life after shooting police officers Fiona Bone and Nicola Hughes in 2012 , was said to have started refusing food at the Category A jail .
He of Cregan was sent to solitary confinement .